text: Malmö FF is an association football club in the town of Malmö in Sweden. The club was established on 24 February 1910. The club has won the Swedish national championship twenty times: in 1944, 1949, 1950, 1951, 1953, 1965, 1967, 1970, 1971, 1974, 1975, 1977, 1986, 1988, 2004, 2010, 2013 2014 2016 2017 2020 2021. They have won the Swedish cup fourteen times (1944, 1946, 1947, 1951, 1953, 1967, 1973, 1974, 1975, 1978, 1980, 1984, 1986 and 1989), which makes them the most successful team in Sweden in history, in terms of the number of titles in these competitions. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official website Category:1910 establishments in Sweden Category:Swedish football clubs Category:Sport in Malmö
